<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id423d7cda-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a" identifier="/us/usc/t26/s241"><num value="241">§ 241.</num><heading> Allowance of special deductions</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">In addition to the deductions provided in part VI (sec. 161 and following), there shall be allowed as deductions in computing taxable income the items specified in this part.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id423d7cdb-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a">(<ref href="/us/act/1954-08-16/ch736">Aug. 16, 1954, ch. 736</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/68A/72">68A Stat. 72</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
